cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with a problem related to computational geometry, specifically the illumination of polygons using wireless devices. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem involves finding an upper bound on the number of devices required, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of an algorithm to achieve the bound indicates that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) may also be relevant. Finally, the use of wireless devices and the concept of illumination may suggest relevance to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
